618. relata] Not only the 11th, but the 15th of the month was devoted to the Carmentali-a. There may have been some confusion between two distinct Carmentae ; indeed, Ovid himself does not identify them, but makes them sisters or companions, inf. 634. The Carmenssa of this latter festival was not a prophetess‚but a sort of Lucina. The carpenta were state-carriages‚ chiefly used for conveying women in sacred processions, but also driven by wealthy fops, Propert. v. 8. 23.
